# Web App — Next.js 16 Conventions

Applies to **everything** inside `apps/web/`. This rule covers the framework
shape. For the 3-layer data flow (actions, services, models), read
`web-server-actions.mdc`. For the AI orchestrator, read
`web-ai-orchestrator.mdc`.

---

## Framework baseline

| Aspect | Value | Notes |
|--------|-------|-------|
| Next.js | **16** (App Router, Turbopack default) | `apps/web/next.config.ts` |
| React | **19** (strict mode enabled) | Server Components by default |
| TypeScript | 5 strict | No `any`; no implicit returns |
| Auth | Clerk (`@clerk/nextjs`) | Provider + proxy + server `auth()` |
| Database | MongoDB Atlas + Mongoose 9 | Singleton connection — see `src/lib/db.ts` |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first) | Shared preset in `@sous/config/tailwind-preset` |
| UI library | shadcn/ui (Radix) | `src/components/ui/` — do not rebuild |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod | Shared schemas in `@sous/types` |
| Data fetching (client) | TanStack Query v5 | See `src/components/shared/providers.tsx` |
| AI (chat) | Vercel AI SDK (`ai`, `@ai-sdk/openai`) | Streaming route handler |
| AI (non-chat) | `openai` npm package | Direct calls from services |
| Billing | Stripe SDK (server) + Stripe.js (client) | Route handlers for checkout/portal |

---

## Clerk middleware is `src/proxy.ts` (Next.js 16)

**Critical:** The file `apps/web/src/proxy.ts` is the Clerk middleware. It is
**not** a typo or a legacy artifact — in Next.js 16 the `middleware.ts`
convention was **renamed to `proxy.ts`** and the exported function name is
now `proxy`. See [Next.js 16 release notes](https://nextjs.org/blog/next-16).

- Do **not** rename `proxy.ts` back to `middleware.ts`.
- Do **not** export a `middleware` function from this file.
- `proxy.ts` runs on the **Node.js runtime** (Edge is no longer supported
  for this convention).
- Public routes are listed inline via `createRouteMatcher`. Any new public
  route (new webhook, new marketing page) must be added there.

```ts
// apps/web/src/proxy.ts
import { clerkMiddleware, createRouteMatcher } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const isPublicRoute = createRouteMatcher([
  "/",
  "/pricing",
  "/api/webhooks/clerk(.*)",
  // ...
]);

export default clerkMiddleware(async (auth, request) => {
  if (!isPublicRoute(request)) {
    await auth.protect();
  }
});
```

