## App Router layout

```
apps/web/src/app/
├── layout.tsx               Root: ClerkProvider + fonts + <Providers>
├── globals.css              Tailwind v4 import + design tokens
├── (dashboard)/             Authenticated app — redirects staff to /staff-blocked
│   └── dashboard/
│       ├── layout.tsx       Location context, LocationSwitcher, AIAssistantPanel
│       ├── page.tsx         Dashboard home
│       ├── schedule/page.tsx + _components/
│       ├── staff/page.tsx   + _components/, [id]/availability/…
│       ├── labor/
│       ├── settings/        (billing, team, ai, locations, schedule-generation)
│       └── time-off/
├── (auth)/                  Sign-in / sign-up surfaces (Clerk components)
├── api/                     Route handlers — see "API routes" below
├── staff-blocked/           Shown when a staff-role user hits the dashboard
├── pricing/                 Marketing
└── features/, sso-callback/ Marketing + Clerk SSO redirect
```

**Rules:**

- Every user-visible route is a Server Component by default. Add
  `"use client"` only when you actually need browser APIs, hooks, or event
  handlers.
- Page-local components live in `_components/` **directly under the page
  that owns them** (underscore prefix excludes them from routing). Don't
  hoist them to `src/components/` unless they're reused across pages.
- Truly shared components live in `src/components/` and are organised by
  intent: `ui/` (shadcn primitives), `shared/` (app-wide widgets like
  `LocationSwitcher`, `ThemeToggle`, `AIAssistantPanel`), `ai-chat/` (chat
  UI primitives), `marketing/` (public-site-only).

### Route group conventions

- `(dashboard)` wraps the entire authenticated surface. Its `layout.tsx`
  calls `auth()` and `getLocationContext(userId)`, redirects staff-role
  users to `/staff-blocked`, and mounts the `LocationSwitcher`, `AIAssistantPanel`,
  and `CustomUserButton`.
- `(auth)` wraps unauthenticated sign-in/up pages and deliberately has no
  Clerk session check.

