## MongoDB / Mongoose usage

- **Only import Mongoose models inside `src/server/services/`.** Actions,
  route handlers, page components, and client components must go through
  a service. This is enforced by convention and code review — linting
  does not catch it.
- Always call `await dbConnect()` at the top of any server code path that
  will touch the database (actions and services already do this via
  `getLocationContext`; ad-hoc scripts do not).
- IDs: services convert string IDs to `new Types.ObjectId(id)` before
  querying. DTOs expose string IDs. Never leak `ObjectId` instances across
  the boundary.
- Services return **DTOs** (plain objects) via `toXDTO(doc.toObject())`.
  Never return a Mongoose Document to an action or UI. This keeps
  serialization safe across the server-action boundary and makes code
  testable.

See `web-server-actions.mdc` for enforced patterns and the 3-layer shape.

