## Common mistakes (do not commit these)

1. Running `npm install` from inside `apps/web/`.
2. Renaming `proxy.ts` → `middleware.ts` (it's the other way round in Next 16).
3. Importing a Mongoose model outside `src/server/services/`.
4. Returning a Mongoose document (`.toObject()` + DTO is required).
5. Reading `orgId` / `locationId` from the client. Always derive server-side
   via `getLocationContext`.
6. Creating a new `src/app/api/*` route for a CRUD mutation (use a Server
   Action).
7. Hardcoding colour hex values instead of CSS variables.
8. Using the `openai` npm package when the Vercel AI SDK is already wired
   (or vice-versa — see `web-ai-orchestrator.mdc` for the rule).
9. Forgetting `"use server"` at the top of a file that exports Server Actions.
10. Exposing `Date` objects from an action (they survive the RSC boundary,
    but downstream JSON serialization will break — DTO them to ISO strings
    when needed).
